0 g cranberry sauce (jelly)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g brandy"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ - 1 tsp hot English mustard"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","2054 kJ \/ 489 kcal","47 g","14 g","26 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["If your turkey breast roll is not secured with string or a net, you will need to secure it with kitchen string to ensure it holds its shape during steaming. Most butchers or specialty poultry providers sell turkey roast rolls pre-wrapped.","Marinate your turkey roll in the sauce overnight to infuse the flavour into the meat. The turkey meat will have a purple hue after steaming though.","To add some colour to your turkey roll fry just before serving in a medium-sized non-stick frying pan over a high heat until golden.","This recipe is a great oven space saver at Christmas time. It removes the big turkey from the oven, allowing more room for other roast meats and vegetables.","This is a great entertaining recipe all-year-round. If you can't find turkey roast rolls outside of the festive season, substitute with a chicken roast roll instead."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 30m","6 portions"]}